UNITED STATES, Libelant-Appellant, v. Steam Tugs N. B. STARBUCK, WHITE ASH, FRED B. DALZELL, JR., E. S. ATWOOD, and W. F. DALZELL, Their Engines, etc.; W. Freeland Dalzell, Claimant-Appellee; Fred B. Dalzell & Co., Inc., Respondent-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 19, 1928. No. 82. Charles H. Tuttle, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Horace M. Gray, Sp. Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for the United States. Burlingham, Veeder, Masten & Fearey, of New York City (Chauncey I. Clark and Frederic Conger, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with costs.
